  "general_form": "fuel (C, H) + O2 -> CO2 + H2O",
  "summary": "A fuel made of carbon and hydrogen burns in oxygen. Complete combustion sends every carbon to carbon dioxide and every hydrogen to water. Because a free element (O2) becomes combined, combustion is always a redox reaction.",
